  "prompt": "How do l see who viewed my videos on Instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can see who viewed your videos if they are part of a story or a reel. Here\u2019s how to check viewer counts for each:\n\n### For Instagram Stories:\n1. **Open Instagram**: Launch the app on your device.\n2. **Go to Your Story**: Tap on your profile picture at the top of the home feed to view your Story.\n3. **Swipe Up**: While viewing your Story, swipe up on the screen. This will show you the list of users who viewed each Story.\n\n### For Instagram Reels:\n1. **Open Instagram**: Launch the app.\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Tap on your profile picture in the bottom right corner.\n3. **Select the Reel**: Tap on the specific reel you want to check.\n4. **View Insights**: Below the reel, you'll see the total view count, but you won't see a specific list of viewers like you do with Stories. Instagram doesn\u2019t provide a list of users who viewed Reels.\n\n### For Regular Video Posts:\nUnfortunately, Instagram does not provide user-specific viewer information for regular video posts. You can see the number of views, but not who viewed them.\n\nRemember that if your account is private, only your followers will be able to view your Stories and Reels, and therefore only they will show up in the viewer list. If your account is public, anyone can view your content without following you.",
